write a Python function to do a case insensitive sort of a list of strings
def case_insensitive_sort(list): 
    return sorted([x.lower() for x in list], key=str.lower)
```This function takes a list of strings as input and returns the same list with all elements sorted in a case-insensitive manner using the `sorted()` function from the builtin library along with a lambda expression to convert each string element to lowercase before sorting it.`
